Working with git and Pelican


Initial setup:

1. Set up name of repository in github  (like filipmu.github.io)
2. Name the directory with the local respository as filipmu.github.io
3. Make sure to rename the 'output' directory as 'docs' for github pages.
3. Initialize the respository by:

git init


4. Do the original commit by:

git add .
git commit -m "initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/filipmu/filipmu.github.io.git
git push -u origin main

5. Do subsequent commits as:

git add .
git commit -m "subsequent commit"
git push -u origin main


After editing Run Pelican:

make html
make serve
make publish
mv output docs


